      • toString

        public java.lang.String toString(commonj.sdo.Type sourceType,
                        java.lang.Object value)
        Converts the given value to a string. Uses java.util.Arrays formatting if an array of objects of the target type is detected.
        Throws:
        InvalidDataConversionException - if the given source type cannot be converted to string as per the SDO 2.1 datatype conversion table.
        java.lang.IllegalArgumentException - if the given value is not the expected Java type as per the SDO 2.1 specification
        Parameters:
        sourceType - the target datatype
        value - the value to convert
        Returns:
        the string value

      • toString

        public java.lang.String toString(commonj.sdo.Property property,
                        java.lang.Object value)
        Converts the given value to a string. Uses java.util.Arrays formatting if the target property is a 'many' property. If an array of objects of the target type is detected for the given value, and the given property is not a 'many' property, an IllegalArgumentException is thrown.
        Throws:
        InvalidDataConversionException - If an array of objects of the target type is detected for the given value, and the given property is not a 'many' property
        java.lang.IllegalArgumentException - if the given value is not the expected Java type as per the SDO 2.1 specification
        java.lang.IllegalArgumentException - if an array of objects of the target type is detected for the given value, and the given property is not a 'many' property
        Parameters:
        sourceProperty - the property type for the given property
        value - the value to convert
        Returns:
        the string value

      • fromString

        public java.lang.Object fromString(commonj.sdo.Type targetType,
                          java.lang.String value)
        Converts the given string value to an object appropriate for the target type. If java.util.Arrays formatting is detected for the given string value, the formatting is removed and the arrays converted into a list of elements appropriate for the target type.
        Parameters:
        targetType - the target data type
        value - the value
        Returns:
        the converted value

      • fromString

        public java.lang.Object fromString(commonj.sdo.Property targetProperty,
                          java.lang.String value)
        Converts the given string value to an object appropriate for the target property and its type. If the given property is a 'many' property, java.util.Arrays formatting is expected. Any java.util.Arrays formatting is removed and the arrays converted into a list of elements appropriate for the target type.
        Throws:
        java.lang.IllegalArgumentException - if the given property is a 'many' property and no java.util.Arrays formatting is detected for the given value.
        Parameters:
        targetType - the target data type
        value - the value to convert from string
        Returns:
        the converted value
